description.narrative: (Cambodia): .FY 2020 funds will be used to educate local community members and representatives about land and natural resources rights, freedom of expression, civil rights, indigenous rights and advocacy skills. These community members and representatives will also be trained as grassroots advocates who defend the rights of their communities, especially on land and natural resources, support community-led campaigns to advocate for land and natural resource issues and provide venues for fair and peaceful solutions to human rights violations. This activity will promote participation of community members--especially women and youth--in decision-making at the local level, support monitoring and investigation of rights violations, and provide protection, including legal aid and representation, to community representatives and activists who are unjustly persecuted...The activity supports Mission Objective 1.2 (CDCS DO1) "Strengthened credible voices to promote fundamental democratic principles and human rights" by advancing the respect for and protection of human rights of the Cambodian people. It falls under the Administration priority to "Advance American Influence" (National Security Strategy, Pillar IV) by addressing human rights violations in Cambodia. The activity also supports the Indo-Pacific Strategy under the Indo-Pacific Transparency Initiative (IPTI)'s Human Rights domain. The activity is being implemented through a grant awarded to ADHOC based on the organization's unique qualifications. .. .
